Ensure the receipt of Bank Statements monthly or request copies of monthly snapshots to facilitate preparation of Bank Reconciliation Statements promptly and in order that reconciling items be identified and adjusted accordingly;
Make necessary and appropriate adjustments for the long-outstanding book reconciling items based on a pertinent document to come up with the correct balance of Cash in Bank accounts;
Improve cash management to avoid incurrence of cash deficits and assertively pursue feasible solutions that can address the issue involving fiscal operations of the Municipality; and
Comply with the reportorial requirements as prescribed by the above-cited rules and regulations.

We recommended that:
The Municipal Budget Officer ensure that the Certified Statement of Indebtedness was fully deliberated and details are properly incorporated in the annual budget to ensure appropriations for the settlement of the existing loan commitments;
Loan amortizations, interests and other expenses related thereto should only be paid out with an duly approved appropriation ordinances prior to the disbursements;
The agreed terms and conditions stipulated in the Loan Agreement should be fully complied by the Management to avoid any possible breaches which may be enforced against the LGU;
Management submit the duly approved Ordinances particularly those which required the review/comments of the Sangguniang Panlalawigan;
The Annual Budget for the subsequent years should incorporate specific appropriations for loan amortizations, interests and other charges; and
Management strictly comply with the above-stated laws.

We recommended Management to:
Conduct reconciliation of records of concerned offices particularly on budget reporting and fund utilization to avoid inconsistencies in the balances of the LDRRM Fund;
Ensure that the unexpended balances of the Continuing Appropriation for LDRRM be maintained in the General Fund books;
Give priority for the inclusion of appropriation for stockpiling of other basic emergency supplies and for the construction of a permanent and disaster-resilient evacuation center which is compliant with DILG Memorandum Circular No. 122, series of 2018 dated August 8, 2018; and
Adhere with all the rules and regulations laid out relative to LDRRM Fund.

We recommended Management to:
Strictly utilize the Quick Response Fund with a duly supported Declaration of State of Calamity stating thereat the specific criteria as enumerated in NDRRMC Memorandum Order No. 60, s. 2019 dated June 17, 2019;
Ensure the timely implementation of projects and utilization of funds to be able to efficiently deliver the immediate needs and relief of calamity or disaster victims;
Efficiently implement programs, projects and activities that are within the LDRRMP and AIP or to its supplemental or revised plans, if any;
Require the Municipal Budget Officer to prepare and maintain Registry of Appropriation, Allotments and Obligations for QRF, MOOE and Capital Outlay; and
Strictly and prudently comply with all the rules and regulations laid out relative to LDRRM Fund.

We recommended Management to:

